# ChummerGenSR4 — Complete Application Analysis

> [!NOTE]
> This document provides an exhaustive breakdown of the ChummerGenSR4 desktop application (a Shadowrun 4th Edition character generator) for the purpose of recreating it as a web application.

---

## 1. High-Level Architecture

ChummerGenSR4 is a **C# WinForms MDI (Multiple Document Interface)** application built with .NET Framework (Visual Studio 2014 / .NET 4.x). It follows a loosely-MVC pattern but is predominantly a **code-behind + rich domain model** architecture.

### Technology Stack
| Component | Technology |
|---|---|
| Language | C# (.NET Framework 4.x) |
| UI Framework | Windows Forms (WinForms) |
| Data Format | XML (both game data and character saves) |
| Persistence | File-based XML (character `.chum` files) |
| Settings | XML settings files + Windows Registry |
| Localization | Custom XML-based i18n system |
| Online Features | SOAP Web Services (Omae) |

### Application Flow
```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Program.Main] --> B[LanguageManager.Load]
    B --> C[frmMain - MDI Parent]
    C --> D{User Action}
    D -->|New Character| E[frmSelectBP - Build Method]
    E --> F[frmMetatype - Race Selection]
    F --> G[frmCreate - Character Creation]
    D -->|Open File| H[Character.Load]
    H -->|Created=false| G
    H -->|Created=true| I[frmCareer - Career Mode]
    G -->|Save as Created| I
```

