## 4. The Improvement System

**File**: [clsImprovement.cs](file:///f:/Projects/ChummerDesktop/Chummer/clsImprovement.cs) — **2,819 lines**

This is the **rules engine** — the most critical system for a web recreation.

### 4.1 How It Works
Improvements are **modifiers** applied to character stats. When a Quality, Cyberware, Spell, or any other object grants a bonus, it creates `Improvement` objects rather than directly modifying values. This allows clean add/remove.

### 4.2 Improvement Data Structure
| Property | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| ImprovedName | string | Target (e.g., "BOD", skill name) |
| SourceName | string | What created it (Quality name, etc.) |
| ImproveType | ImprovementType enum | What kind (Attribute, Skill, Armor, etc.) |
| ImproveSource | ImprovementSource enum | Source category (Quality, Cyberware, etc.) |
| Value, Minimum, Maximum, Augmented, AugmentedMaximum | int | Numeric modifiers |
| Rating | int | Source item's rating |
| Exclude | string | Exceptions to the improvement |
| UniqueName | string | Grouping — only highest in group applies |
| AddToRating | bool | Applies to skill Rating vs dice pool |
| Enabled | bool | Active or disabled |

### 4.3 ImprovementType Enum (89 types)
Covers: Skill, Attribute, BallisticArmor, ImpactArmor, Reach, Nuyen, Essence, Reaction, PhysicalCM, StunCM, UnarmedDV, SkillGroup, SkillCategory, InitiativePass, MatrixInitiative, LifestyleCost, CMThreshold, WeaponCategoryDV, CyberwareEssCost, SpecialTab, LivingPersona stats, Smartlink, BiowareEssCost, MovementPercent, FreePositiveQualities, FreeNegativeQualities, NuyenMaxBP, AdeptPowerPoints, DamageResistance, DrainResistance, FadingResistance, Composure, JudgeIntentions, Memory, and many more.

### 4.4 ImprovementManager (lines 826–2818)
| Method | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `ValueOf(type, addToRating, improvedName)` | Sum all active improvements of a given type |
| `CreateImprovements(source, sourceName, xmlNode, ...)` | Parse XML bonus nodes and create improvement objects |
| `RemoveImprovements(source, sourceName)` | Remove all improvements from a source |
| `CreateImprovement(...)` | Create a single improvement and add to transaction |
| `Commit()` | Finalize transaction |
| `Rollback()` | Undo transaction |

The `CreateImprovements` method (lines 1124–2460, **1,300+ lines**) is a massive switch/if-else chain that handles every possible XML bonus node type.

