## 9. Data Flow Patterns

### 9.1 Adding an Item (e.g., Quality)
```
1. User clicks "Add Quality" button
2. frmCreate.cmdAddQuality_Click()
3. Opens frmSelectQuality dialog
4. Dialog loads qualities.xml via XmlManager
5. Filters by BookXPath (enabled sourcebooks)
6. User selects → returns Quality XML node
7. Quality.Create(xmlNode, ...) called
8. ImprovementManager.CreateImprovements() processes <bonus> XML
9. Creates Improvement objects for each bonus
10. ImprovementManager.Commit() adds to Character._lstImprovements
11. Quality added to Character._lstQualities
12. TreeNode added to TreeView
13. CalculateBP() recalculates all build points
14. UI labels updated
```

### 9.2 Removing an Item
```
1. User selects item in TreeView, clicks Delete
2. Find object via CommonFunctions.FindX()
3. ImprovementManager.RemoveImprovements(source, name)
4. Each removed improvement may trigger side effects
5. Object removed from Character list
6. TreeNode removed
7. CalculateBP() recalculated
```

### 9.3 Saving a Character
```
Character.Save() → XmlTextWriter
  ├── Write scalar fields (name, metatype, karma, etc.)
  ├── Write attributes (each Attribute.Save())
  ├── For each collection:
  │   ├── Skills, SkillGroups, Contacts, Spells, Powers...
  │   └── Each object.Save(writer) serializes its own fields
  ├── Write Improvements list
  ├── Write Expenses list
  └── Write organizational data (locations, bundles, groups)
```

