## 10. Key Architectural Observations for Web Recreation

### Separation of Concerns (Current)
| Layer | Implementation | Issues |
|---|---|---|
| Data/Model | `cls*.cs` files | Well-structured domain objects |
| Business Logic | Mixed into `Character` + `ImprovementManager` | Improvement engine is sound but coupled to WinForms (MessageBox calls) |
| UI | `frm*.cs` files | **Massively coupled** — 23K+ lines per form with logic embedded |
| Data Access | `XmlManager` | Clean XML caching system |
| Persistence | `Character.Save/Load` | XML serialization built into domain objects |

### Critical Systems to Replicate
1. **Improvement System** — The rules engine. Must be faithfully reproduced.
2. **XML Data Loading** — All game content comes from XML. Convert to JSON or keep XML with a parser.
3. **Build Point / Karma Calculation** — Complex validation and spending logic.
4. **Attribute System** — Base/augmented/metatype limits with improvement modifiers.
5. **Equipment Nesting** — Gear contains Gear, Cyberware contains Cyberware, Vehicles contain Mods contain Weapons contain Accessories contain Gear.
6. **Expense Tracking** — Full undo support for career mode.
7. **Character Serialization** — Save/Load format compatibility.

### What Can Be Simplified
- **TreeView coupling** — The original passes WinForms TreeNodes into domain objects. Web version should keep UI separate.
- **Duplicate code** — frmCreate and frmCareer share ~60% of their logic but are separate 23K/27K line files.
- **Find methods** — CommonFunctions has dozens of nearly-identical search methods. A generic finder pattern would reduce this.
- **Settings** — 100+ boolean options could be a configuration object with defaults.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `ImprovementManager.CreateImprovements()` method (1,300+ lines) is the single most critical piece of logic. It is the **rules engine** that translates XML bonus definitions into concrete stat modifications. Any web recreation **must** faithfully replicate this logic or the character generator will produce incorrect results.
